            h2.subtitle-1 Chiropractic
            p Chiropractic is a licensed health care profession that addresses problems affecting the musculoskeletal system. Chiropractors treat back pain, neck pain, joint pain, and headaches.
            h3.heading-1 How it Works
            p Chiropractors correct joint problems with manual adjustments. This improves the quality of complex movement patterns. Chiropractic adjustments also stimulate the nervous system, which causes a release of chemicals that affect the muscles, spinal cord, and brain. This stimulates healing and reduces pain. Evidence suggests that chiropractic adjusments may help to prevent injury, as well as treat it.
